You have to spend the time to build a solid foundation of anything before you start branching out, kinda how you don’t have to explain rap but that has to be done by people with the most spotlight. Unfortunately when they get big enough they start becoming “ artist” leaving grime in the shadows, only to revisit when credentials are on the line. And we all love JAY-Z, but Kano, Wiley and all those (Purists) need to be uplifted for grime to get the respect it deserves world wide.

snippet.textDisplay:
Another black man where the most important thing to him is his blackness. Genuinely had no clue about race or stigma attached to it until I met black folk. People think white people are racist. Black people are just as bad with their own. They pressurise other black men (in the main) into their interpretation of blackness, and black lads who aren't interested in their race or who understand that their culture holds them back in certain aspects of life are treated as white sympathisers and branded names such as choc ice. Racism will unfortunately exist until you stop defining yourself by the colour of your skin.

As a side note, there are aspects of white, western European culture that holds us back too. However, I've never heard a white Male ever define himself as a white male unless hes apologising for historical events in a room with other ethnicities. And I dont believe we promote our societal culture over that of the individual.
